VESICULAR STOMATITIS - USA (ARIZONA)
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Vesicular stomatitis: a brief summary 971002093841
Vesicular stomatitis, horse - USA (Arizona) 970614154134
Date: Wed, 24 Sep 1997
From: Sharon Rose <fasstudy@fas.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, Vol 10, No 42

Second outbreak in Arizona: Text of a fax received on 22 October 1997 from
Dr J.M. Arnoldi, Deputy Administrator, Veterinary Services, United States
Department of Agriculture, Washington, DC
End of previous report period for Arizona: 6 June 1997. End of this report
period: 22 October 1997.
New outbreaks:
Location No. of outbreaks
Maricopa county, 1
State of Arizona
Total number of positive cases since 1 January 1997: 275 (190 in Colorado,
63 in New Mexico, 20 in Utah and 2 in Arizona).
Total number of animals in the new outbreak:
species susceptible cases deaths destroyed slaughtered
horse 9 1* 0 0 0
* Arab mare
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: National Veterinary Services
Laboratories, Ames, Iowa.
B. Diagnostic tests used: positive virus isolation with compatible clinical
signs.
C. Causal agent: typing in progress.
Epidemiology: investigations pending; case control study in progress.
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: unknown.
B. Mode of spread: current evidence suggests that this was an imported case.
The affected mare is part of a group of horses returning from a horse show
in Durango (in active positive area in Colorado).
Control measures during reporting period: quarantine, starting on 11
October 1997, placed on affected premises by the State of Arizona.
--
Sharon Rose
ProMED/AHEAD Associate
<fasstudy@fas.org>
